status word definition


 0   level3   
 1   level3
 2   level3
 3   level3
 4   preselectedevents
 5   charge
 6   charge
 7   charge
 8   momentum sign
 9   velocity sign
10   track pattern
11   track pattern
12   track pattern
13   track pattern
14   track pattern
15   beta pattern
16   beta pattern
17   ctc layers fired
18   ctc layers fired
19   anti sector fired
20   anti sector fired
21   npart found
22   npart found
23   rigidity range
24   -----
25   track quality
26   ------
27   geomagnetic latitude
28   geomagnetic latitude
29   localdbused 
30   event has errors
31   status not found




level3:
0-15 As described in trigger3.h

prescaledevents:
bit 0 set:    prescaled event 

charge:
0   charge 1
1   charge 2
2   charge 3
3   charge 4
4   charge 5
5   charge 6
6   charge 7
7   charge >=8

momentum sign:
0    -
1    +

velocity sign
0    -
1    +

tracker pattern
see datacards.doc

beta pattern
0    4 hits
1    3 hits
2    2 hits

ctc layers
0   0 layers
1   1 layer
2   2 layers


anti sector
0   0
1   1
2   2
3   >=3


npart 
0   0
1   1
2   2
3   >=3

rigidity (abs)
0  <2 GV
1  <8 GV
2  <20 GV
3  >20 GV

track quality
0  - at least 4S+4K with high threshold
1  - at least 4S+4K
2  - at least 4S+3K
3  - at least 4S

geomagnetic latitude
0 < 10 degres  cos <0.1736
1 < 30 degrees cos <0.5
2 < 50 degrees cos < 0.766
3 > 50 degrees cos > 0.766

localdb used for tracker alignment
0   //not used
1   // used

error bit
0 no error
1    error

correspondance between bits & status datacards words:

values 0123...etc --> 1 10 100 1000    (in fact base ESTA 34)
                      0 in datacards means select everything




N.B.

Due to lack of bits there is no "undefined state" bits,
so to ensure proper functionality one has to require 
particle (datacards: ESTA 10=1110) for most other status bits
